07/05/2004
ATHENS, Greece -- Hellenic Army Chief of General Staff Lieutenant General Panagiotis Harvalas submitted his resignation on Thursday (6 May), reportedly in response to recent accidents involving army personnel.
The defence ministry accepted the resignation without public comment.
In other developments, Canada's National Defence General Staff Chief P.P.
Henault arrives for a weeklong official visit Friday.
He will be discussing possibilities for bilateral co-operation to achieve common goals.
(MPA - 06/05/04)
